10000*(0.5*1.8 + 0.5*0.4)^{52}
V(52) = 10000 *1.8^X *0.4^{n-X}
X \sim bin(n,p)
n=52
p=0.5
X
np=26
V(52) = 10000 *1.8^{26} *0.4^{52-26}
X
E[X]
X
V
E[V] = \sum_{x=0}^{52} (10000) (1.8)^x (0.4)^{52-x} \binom{52}{x} (0.5)^x (0.5)^{52-x}
= 10000 \sum_{x=0}^{52} \binom{52}{x} (0.9)^x (0.2)^{52-x} = 10000 (1.1)^{52},
